[3] USA (Virginia)
Date: 20 May 2015
Source: NBC Washington [edited]
http://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/Measles-Case-Confirmed-in-Fairfax-County-304324971.html


Health Officials have confirmed a new case of measles in Fairfax County, VA. And the infected person visited sites in Washington and Fairfax County before the diagnosis. Now health officials are letting people know where the person visited in case anyone has contracted the disease.

Measles is highly contagious, spread through coughing, sneezing and contact with secretions from the nose, mouth and throat of an infected person. However, people who have been vaccinated are at very low risk of the disease.

Symptoms of measles can include fever greater than 101 degrees, runny nose, watery red eyes and cough, followed by a blotchy rash that appears on the face and spreads to the rest of the body. Symptoms usually appear within 7 to 21 days after exposure. If you or a member of your family believe you have been exposed, are not vaccinated and have symptoms of the disease, contact your health care provider. Please call ahead before going to the doctor's office or the emergency room and tell them that you may have been exposed to measles.

Here is where and when the infected person was and may have exposed others:

- Embassy Suites, 900 10th St., NW Washington, D.C. on Sun 10 May 10 - Fri 15 May 2015, all hours. Health department to call: D.C. Dept. of Health,
202-420-0199.

- IFC Building, 2121 Pennsylvania Ave., NW Washington, D.C. Mon 11 May 2015, 7am-2pm. Health department to call: D.C. Dept. of Health, 202-420-0199

- Inova Fairfax Medical Campus, Emergency Department. 3300 Gallows Road, Falls Church, Va. Tue 12 May 2015, 10am-5pm. Health department to call: Fairfax County 703-267-3511

- Inova Fairfax Medical Campus, North Tower (Floors 6-11). 3300 Gallows Road, Falls Church, Va. Fri 15 May 2015, 3:30 pm to Sat 16 May 2015 at 3 p.m. Health department to call: Fairfax County HD 703-267-3511

- Inova Fairfax Medical Campus, North Tower (Lobby). 3300 Gallows Road, Falls Church, Va. Fri 15 May 3:30-7 pm and Sat 16 May 2015, 7-10:30 a.m. Health department to call: Fairfax County HD 703-267-3511

- Inova Fairfax Medical Campus, Women's and Children's Bldg. (Ground Level & Basement). 3300 Gallows Road, Falls Church, Va. Fri 15 May 15, 3:30-7 p.m. and Sat 16 May 2015, 7-10:30 a.m. Health department to call: Fairfax County HD, 703-267-3511

- Woodburn Medical Park Building #2. 3289 Woodburn Road, Annandale, Va. Fri 15 May 2015, 9:30 a.m.-5 p.m. Health department to call: Fairfax County HD 703-267-3511

- The Shelby Apartments, 6200 N. Kings Highway Alexandria, Va. Sun 10 May 2015, 10 a.m.-10 p.m. through Fri 15 May 2015, 3-7 p.m. Health department to call: Fairfax County HD 703-267-3511

