[5] Taiwan
Date: 27 may 2015
Source: China Post [edited]
http://www.chinapost.com.tw/health/infectious-diseases/2015/05/27/436999/Measles-diagnoses.htm.


3 more cases linked to the Ever Rich Duty-free shop in Neihu Airport [Taiwan Taoyuan International is an international airport serving the capital city of Taiwan - Mod.CP] Taipei, and the northern parts of the country. Located about 40 km west of Taipei in Dayuan District, Taoyuan City, Taiwan, the airport is Taiwan's largest airport. The 3 additional cases of measles were confirmed by the Centers for Disease Control (CDC, Taiwan), yesterday, adding to the total number of diagnoses in a case of group infections starting from the Ever Rich Duty Free Shop in Neihu, according to CDC officials.

On 19 May 2015, the CDC confirmed that 4 colleagues working at the Ever Rich Duty Free Shop in Neihu were infected with measles. According to the CDC, the disease may have been passed by foreign visitors, most likely from a group from mainland China that had just been to the shop. For precautionary reasons, most employees of Ever Rich have been asked to be vaccinated against the disease, officials added.

According to officials, another 3 cases of measles were confirmed yesterday, with 2 men and a woman coming down with the disease. The total diagnoses of this group infection case have now reached 7 individuals. Officials said that the 3 patients confirmed yesterday had been in personal contact with the 4 workers from Ever Rich.

Measles is a highly infectious respiratory disease that is spread by contact with droplets from the nose, mouth or throat of an infected person, either directly or through aerosol transmission. With the increasing number of diagnoses, the number of people in contact with the patients is growing, making it more and more difficult for the CDC to launch preventative measures and trace all contacts back for examination.

According to the CDC, the female patient went on 13 May 2015 to MYST, a night club at ATT 4 FUN, and then took the MRT from Zhongxiao Fuxing Station to Ximen Station on the morning of 14 May 2015; 1 of the male patients commutes daily between MRT Longshan Temple Station and Ximen Station.

The number of people in contact with the patients has now reached 1668, among whom 216 have yet to be tracked down for examination. According to the CDC, an infected person remains infectious 4 days before and after the development of rash. Physicians are urged to remain vigilant for suspected cases. If symptoms such as fever, rhinitis, conjunctivitis, and a rash develop, patients are to seek immediate medical advice, reduce the possibility of further transmission, and inform medical authorities of relevant travel and exposure history.

Deputy Director-General of the CDC Chou Chih-ha reminded that people who were at the Ever Rich Duty Free Shop in Neihu from 23 Apr to 21 May 2015, or any of the other locations mentioned above, should be extremely attentive for any symptoms.

[Byline: Sun Hsin]

--
