ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to the China Post of 29 May 2015, 12 cases of measles have been diagnosed so far in 2015; 3 additional cases of measles were identified yesterday, increasing the total number of diagnoses to 12 so far this year, revealed the Centers for Disease Control.

A 31-year-old woman, as well as 2 men aged 27 and 28, were confirmed to be infected with measles yesterday. All 3 work at the Ever Rich Duty Free Shop Neihu branch, where the contagious disease was 1st reported on 19 May 2015. The latest diagnoses bring the total number of infections at the duty-free shop to 10, in addition to the 1930 individuals known to have had direct contact with the infected persons, 346 of whom are still being tracked down for examination.

Officials revealed the locations that the 3 patients have visited recently, warning that anyone who has been in contact with the infected individuals or has visited the areas should be attentive to any symptoms and remain in isolation for 18 days if possible.

Locations include MRT Qizhang Station, Sun Yat-Sen Memorial Hall Station, Taipei Main Station's Suddenly Hair salon, Second Floor Cafe, Vie Show Cinemas Taipei Q Square, Xindian Household Registration Office, Tri-Service General Hospital, Taishin International Bank Xindian Branch, Taiwan Cooperative Bank Liouhe Branch and Xindian Wufeng Post Office.

According to the CDC, upon discovery of symptoms such as fever, rhinitis, conjunctivitis or rash, patients are to seek immediate medical attention, avoid potential transmission and inform medical authorities of relevant travel and exposure history. See: http://www.chinapost.com.tw/taiwan/national/national-news/2015/5/29/437131/Twelve-cases.htm

Furthermore measles Diagnoses has been growing worldwide. More than 35 000 cases of measles infection have been confirmed so far in 2015 around the world, with 40 percent found in Western Pacific areas and Africa, officials said. Sustained spread of the disease has been reported in China, which has accumulated more than 22 700 diagnoses from January to April 2015; the disease also hit Mongolia hard in March 2015.

According to the [Taiwan] CDC, 12 cases of measles have been confirmed in the nation so far in 2015, 11 of which were local residents, and the other a mainland China national. - Mod.CP]

